{"lemma":"قُنْفُذِ","slug":"قُنْفُذِ","root":"ق.ن.ف.ذ","root_slug":"ق-ن-ف-ذ","root_link":"/words/roots/ق-ن-ف-ذ","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n42848"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%82%D9%8F%D9%86%D9%92%D9%81%D9%8F%D8%B0%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"hedgehog"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Considering the spirantization of the final consonant, and the occasional variation of the second syllable with fatḥa, borrowed from Aramaic קֻפְדָּא / קוּפְּדָּא (qupdā) / ܩܽܘܦܕܳܐ (quppəḏā), which in Classical Mandaic is written out ࡒࡅࡍࡐࡅࡃ (qunpud), as also in Samaritan Aramaic ࠒࠍࠐࠃ (qnfd) beside ࠒࠐࠃ (qfd), also likely the source of Hebrew קִפּוֹד (qippṓḏ), all meaning hedgehog. Compare Arabic خُنْفُس (ḵunfus, “beetle”) as a borrowing with a similar form, where the main Aramaic dialects do not display the /n/ insertion.\nRelated to meanings of the root ק־פ־ד / ܩ ܦ ܕ / ق ف د (q f d) “to be wrinkled, to be twisted up, to wind, to roll entirely round”."},"ipa":["/qun.fuð/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n42848","headword_ar":"قُنْفُذ","root":"qnf*","body":[{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^aboyaDu $aTorFA A^asowadu ZahorFA yamo$iY qimoTarFA wayabuwlu qaTorFA","text_ar":"مَا اَبْيَضُ شَطْرًا اَسْوَدُ ظَهْرًا يَمْشِى قِمْطَرًا وَيَبُولُ قَطْرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"In the original text, the page break is before the final word of the preceding text."},{"kind":"page_break","n":2994},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What is white in one half, black in the back, that walks contractedly, and makes water in drops?"},{"kind":"text","text":"An enigma: to which the answer is, The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qunofu*","text_ar":"قُنْفُذ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (L.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qunofu*u layolK","text_ar":"قُنْفُذُ لَيْلٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One who sleeps not"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"during the night"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; because the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qnf*","text_ar":"قنفذ"},{"kind":"text","text":"sleeps not: (L:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a calumniator; a slanderer;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anoqadu layolK","text_ar":"اَنْقَدُ لَيْلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.) ―         -b3-  Also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qunofu*N","text_ar":"قُنْفُذٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qunofa*N","text_ar":"قُنْفَذٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mouse;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faArN","text_ar":"فَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) fem. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qunofu*N","text_ar":"قُنْفُذٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part behind the ear"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a camel,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whence the sweat exudes."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K.) ―         -b5-  And, with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part of the head that is below that which is called the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qamaHoduwap","text_ar":"قَمَحْدُوَة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qunofu*N","text_ar":"قُنْفُذٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place that produces tangled herbage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an elevated place abounding with trees:"},{"kind":"text","text":"AHn says, that what is thus termed is in hard ground, between what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quf~","text_ar":"قُفّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and sand. (L.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qunofu*u ramolK","text_ar":"قُنْفُذُ رَمْلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sand collected together,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Kheyreh, L, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and elevated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"somewhat elevated:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Kheyreh, L:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abundance of trees of sand:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qunofa*u ramolK","text_ar":"قُنْفَذُ رَمْلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h, signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abundance and tallness of trees of sand."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qunofu*N","text_ar":"قُنْفُذٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K) and with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A tree in the midst of sand."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K.) ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qanaAfi*u","text_ar":"قَنَافِذُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Mountains that are not long:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"long and narrow tracts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHobul","text_ar":"اَحْبُل"},{"kind":"text","text":", L, K, TA: in the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajobul","text_ar":"اَجْبُل"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mountains,"},{"kind":"text","text":") of sand: (L, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hills with pointed heads"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabakN","text_ar":"نَبَكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lying in the way,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"road."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Th, L, K.)"}],"source_refs":["L","K","S"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}